item.title: CVE-2016-7056|2024-08-06T01:50:46.703Z -- the%20openssl%20project -- openssl
item.description: A timing attack flaw was found in OpenSSL 1.0.1u and before that could allow a malicious user with local access to recover ECDSA P-256 private keys.
